ce:section.ce:para:
The CDs@SiO2 were fabricated according to the reported method [30]. Just the 25 ml blue CDs took the place of 25 ml water in the bCDs@SiO2 synthesis procedure and the mesoporous particles (r-CDs@MSN) were obtained after refluxing the CDs@SiO2 with acetone. From the SEM images (Fig. 3
                        ), the shape of SiO2 is spherical and the diameter of SiO2 is about 150 nm (Fig. 3a). Combining with CDs and refluxed were having no effect on surface morphology and particle size. The CDs@SiO2 also appears spherical (Fig. 3b) but its diameter is 30 nm smaller than SiO2, which is about 120 nm. After refluxing, the average size of r-CDs@MSN (Fig. 3c) has not changed much approximately 120 nm. It can be inspected more clearly from TEM image (Fig. 4
                        ), illustrating that the r-CDs@ MSN is spherical morphology and the average size is 130 nm, which is consistent with the results of scanning electron microscopy. The middle of the sphere is darker and the edge is getting grey, conforming to the core-shell structure. Making r-CDs@MSN as a drug-loading system, it is easier access to the body and facilitate the phagocytosis of cells due to such small particle size, improving the drug efficacy and diminishing toxicity.
